events.name: Google Cloud Study Jam
events.description:
• What we'll do
Study Jams are community-run study groups for students on Google Developers content, on various product topics.
The objective of Study Jams is to raise the technical proficiency of our global community members through the highest possible course completion rate.

Why attend a study jam?

Your will:
- Learn how to set up development and production environments in the Cloud.
- Learn how Docker and Kubernetes work, or learn how to process Big Data in the Cloud.
- Get access to Qwiklabs.com, a Google training tool, free of charge (a $70+ value).
- Get Google-hosted badges like this for their online profiles, to show potential employers what they
know about Cloud computing.

• What to bring
Notebook, Laptop, charger and an extension cable.

• Important to know

events.name: Mobile Site Certification Study Jam
events.description:
• What we'll do
This is a meet-up that will provide access to the professional accreditation that Google offers to individuals who demonstrate understanding in basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development.

We will be a 3 to 4 hour of study material followed by a 90 minute multiple choice exam.

At the end, there will be a printable certificate to verify status as a certified mobile sites professional.

• What to bring
Notebook, pen, laptop, charger, an extension cable (if you can) and some good vibes!

• Important to know

-A mindset for learning

-How to install and use Android Studio
-Understanding android development process
-Creating Android project from a template
-Adding log message to your app for debugging purposes
events.how_to_find_us: hit us in our email: ihubdevelopers@gmail.com incase of any question regarding the workshop

events.name: Android Fundamentals #2
events.description:
Did you know Android is an open source software and Google is a member of Open Handset Alliance (OHA). This means individuals can modify the source code of the OS and add new features.

So lets get started :) :) :)
What you will learn during the meetup:
-How to create an app with interactive behavior.
-How to use the layout editor to design a layout.
-How to edit the layout in XML.
-A lot of new terminology. Check out the Vocabulary words and concepts
glossary for friendly definitions.
https://developers.google.com/android/for-all/vocab-words/
And a lot more

events.name: Android Developer Fundamentals #3
events.description:
Did you know
Android is available in 46 different languages, this also means, apps can be produced in different languages to cover wider audiences, so you can develop a Swahili:) :) :)

Learners will learn :
Activities and Intents
-How to create a new Activity in Android Studio.
-How to define parent and child activities for Up navigation.
-How to start an Activity with an explicit Intent.
-How to pass data between each Activity with an explicit Intent.

events.name: Developers Week
events.description:
With simplified access to telco infrastructure, developers use Africa's Talking powerful SMS, USSD, Voice, Airtime and Payments APIs to bring their ideas to life, as they build and sustain scalable businesses.
Lets learn a variety of communication and payments API products provided by Africa's aTalking that are everything you need to build high impact mobile engagement solutions.

Learners will learn:
1.Building a two factor authentication system using sms
2.Building an offline account management application using USSD
3.Collecting mobile payments from an online shopping cart

Fasten your safety belt and get ready to learn amazing technologies from amazing instructors.

events.name: Google Cloud study Jam
events.description:
Just think about this
" Cloud Computing is up to 40 times more cost-effective for a Small and Medium Business (SMB), compared to running an in-house IT system."
Join us as we learn how you can leverage the power of cloud using Google Cloud Platform and walk away with 1 month free access to qwiklabs and a badge after successfully completing your quest.

Together, we can help solve your toughest problems and grow your businesses. With Google Cloud, Their infrastructure is your infrastructure. Their tools are your tools. And Their innovations are your innovations.

What learners will learn:
Creating a virtual machine
Getting started with cloud shell and gcloud
Provision services with cloud launcher
Creating a persistent disk
A demo to introduction to docker

Hope you are excited as we are organizing this event...

Happy learning.🤘🤘🤘
